        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 4 at 4:16PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 416 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lajitas, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Terlingua and Study Butte.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
